<h2 id="Syntax" name="Syntax">Syntax</h2>

<pre class="twopartsyntaxbox"><code>Formal syntax:  <code>auto <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Single_bar" title="Single bar: The two entities are optional, but exactly one must be present.">|</a> isolate</code></code></pre>

<pre>isolation: auto;
isolation: isolate;

isolation: initial;
isolation: inherit;
isolation: unset;
</pre>

<h3 id="Values" name="Values">Values</h3>

<dl><dt><code>auto</code></dt>
 <dd>Is a keyword indicating that a new stacking context has to be created only if one properties applied to the element requires it.</dd>
 <dt><code>isolate</code></dt>
 <dd>Is a keyword indicating that a new stacking context must be created.</dd>
</dl>